6:
Wow, she's got a whole workshop
set up here...
10:
I wanted to know more about the
tech around here so I was
wandering from place to place, but I
ended up meeting some sponsors
in the process.
14:
Thanks to them, my research is
making great progress! Wahaha!
22:
Are these... android bodies? Did you
create these yourself?
28:
Of course. Fundamentally speaking,
though, they're still controlled like
golems. Golems are versatile, aren't
they?
31:
I'm selling them off in large
quantities, too! Mu-ho-ho-ho!
41:
That's all well and good... But I hear
you haven't been seen very often at
Voluntas Academy, recently.
50:
These are the notes and printouts
from your time away from Luciada.
The Golem Club is worried about
you.
59:
Is there something about the
Academy that's troubling you? For
what it's worth, I'd be happy to
speak with you about it...
63:
Nothing's wrong? I really like it there.
Everyone in the club is great, too.
66:
But, well... I think they could stand to
challenge my golem theories more
often.
68:
But only Luciada or the professor
would ever dare to do so. The rest of
them were too timid to try...
72:
W-well, anyway! I'll see them back
at the Academy once I'm ready to
take a break with my research.
75:
I've got tons of new theories and
tech I want to share with everyone!
81:
She's only human, after all... I wish
there was something we could do to
help.
84:
Hmm... If she's worried about the
others being too concerned about
her feelings, I think the feeling is
mutual...
89:
Tharros? What is it? Have you been
following us?
94: Wait. There's text on the screen...
106:
You want me to help you? Why
would I do that after what you just
pulled off?
109:
We could have been a little less
rough, I admit. But take it as a sign
of our appreciation! We need
someone who can do what you do.
111:
Appreciation, huh?
...I guess you guys are Updaters.
Right?
114:
Right. Yeah, more traditional types
aren't too fond of my work, you know.
117:
Ah, I see! So you've clashed with
stubborn minds too, then!
118:
Minds like that never change...
They're hard-wired to never
question the status quo. Every last
one of them is completely hopeless!
120:
They don't even understand what
change is. They merely seek to
justify their laziness and
incompetence, all while dismissing
us as heretics! If they won't
understand, we'll MAKE them!
122:
So you intend to carry out acts of
destruction, then? I get the
impression that my golem tech
would be able to evade a lot of the
local countermeasures here.
125: Yes, yes! I knew you'd get it!
133:
But your ideology and mine are
nothing alike!
136:
...That's too bad. I guess we're going
to have to do this the hard way, then.
139:
Don't take another step if you want
her in one piece.
146:
Seriously? For someone claiming to
be an advocate of change, this is an
awfully stale strategy you're using.
151:
You guys really shouldn't be
messing with me.
155:
Wh-what the?! My body, i-it moved
on its own
159: Everyone! Let's move while we can!
163:
Wahaha! What do you think of THAT!
That's what happens when you
underestimate me!
166:
But... Why? Why are they suddenly
fighting amongst themselves?
170:
Just because it can be used by an
android, at the end of the day, these
are still golems.
174:
Oh... So you can seize control any
time you want, huh...
178:
Still, thanks for helping me out. Even
with control over the golems, I was
still outnumbered. It would have
been tough to do this alone.
181:
...But it's true. Not too many people
can keep up with someone like me.
184:
But that's why I want to create a
solution to that. I want to make a
way for people to follow after me.
187:
...Even if there comes a time when I
can't stick around anymore.
196:
You and everyone who follows you
will be there.
200: I mean, yeah. You guys too, right?
212:
Why am I under arrest?! We
rounded up all the extremists for
you! You should be awarding us, if
anything!
216:
Ah... Apparently taking control of
someone else's body is a serious
crime around here...
219:
B-but don't worry! I reached out to
some people, and your good deeds
will get you released in just a few
days!
222:
...However, this whole situation's
received extensive press coverage,
so all your sponsors have dropped
out...
226:
W-well, you know... Perhaps this
presents a good opportunity to
return to the Academy?
245:
I'll get your notes and printouts sent
to you while you're away!
251:
Wahhh, no! This sucks!
I'll make all these obstinate fools
pay for this, one day!
255: Being a genius is so lonely!
